			<div class="content" id="post-content-1269857">
									

<p>I cracked a smile, but didn't chuckle. Not because it wasn't funny, but because the joke number threw me off. SCP-500 is too solidly established as the panacea for me to shake it from my head. Wierd, I know, but that was my honest reaction.</p>
<p>I like that it comes across as misogynist. That is kind of the point, in my view. O5-8 is behaving like an over-the-top misogynist ass, and abusing his position to &quot;contain&quot; his unhappy marriage. It doesn't mean that the author is a pig, just the character.</p>
<p>Makes me wonder why there aren't more tales of O5s abusing their nigh-unquestionable authority for personal reasons.</p>

